============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Binomial Theorem
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      (a+b)^n = sum of C(n,k) a^k b^(n-k)
Applications: Probability, statistics, polynomial algebra
Discoverer:   Newton/Pascal (1665)

Theorem/Law:  Pythagorean Theorem
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      a² + b² = c²
Applications: Navigation, construction, computer graphics
Discoverer:   Pythagoras (500)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Nihilism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Life has no inherent meaning; values are human inventions
Philosopher:  Nietzsche (diagnosed)
Example:      Without objective grounding, all moral frameworks are invented

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

